01:57.285 --> 01:59.485
[cell phone ringing]

02:12.167 --> 02:14.067
[phone beeps]

02:14.069 --> 02:16.569
DAMON: Bonnie, hey.

02:16.571 --> 02:17.904
Bonnie!

02:17.906 --> 02:19.806
[crying]

02:19.808 --> 02:22.055
Bonnie, hey, what's wrong?

02:22.058 --> 02:23.958
Is she still alive?

02:26.381 --> 02:27.880
Bonnie, talk to me.

02:27.882 --> 02:29.382
She's okay.

02:29.384 --> 02:31.184
Elena's okay.

02:31.186 --> 02:32.852
Well, those aren't tears of joy, Bon.

02:32.854 --> 02:34.520
What is wrong?

02:35.590 --> 02:37.623
He's gone.

02:39.527 --> 02:40.960
Enzo's gone.

02:40.962 --> 02:43.529
What?

02:45.633 --> 02:47.266
He's dead.

02:47.268 --> 02:49.035
Your brother killed him.

02:52.307 --> 02:53.973
Listen to me, Bonnie.

02:53.975 --> 02:56.075
I am on my way, okay?

02:56.077 --> 02:57.343
No!

02:57.345 --> 02:58.845
Stay away!

02:58.847 --> 03:00.246
Stay away from me.

03:00.248 --> 03:03.549
Not until I know you're safe.

03:03.551 --> 03:05.184
I'll deal with Stefan.

03:07.055 --> 03:08.521
I already did.

03:08.523 --> 03:09.922
What do you mean?

03:09.924 --> 03:12.091
I gave him the cure.

03:13.485 --> 03:15.352
He's human now.

03:21.169 --> 03:24.037
[panting]

03:24.039 --> 03:25.271
No!

03:36.084 --> 03:38.184
[phone ringing]

03:43.992 --> 03:45.625
I'm here.

03:45.627 --> 03:47.894
Stefan, thank God.

03:47.896 --> 03:52.231
I talked to Damon, and I
know what happened to Enzo.

03:52.233 --> 03:55.134
Bonnie... she must be...

03:55.136 --> 03:57.503
I don't even know what to say.

03:57.505 --> 03:59.639
I don't know how I can...

03:59.641 --> 04:02.341
Every time I close my eyes,

04:02.343 --> 04:05.078
I see it play out over
and over again in my head.

04:05.080 --> 04:09.082
And every time I open them, I
see Enzo's blood on my hands.

04:09.084 --> 04:11.317
Just please come home.

04:11.319 --> 04:13.486
I can't do that.

04:13.488 --> 04:14.821
Well, I'm not letting you run.

04:14.823 --> 04:16.755
Okay? So just tell me where you are.

04:16.757 --> 04:17.990
I'm coming to get you.

04:17.992 --> 04:19.425
No.

04:19.427 --> 04:22.261
I can't face you, and
I can't face Bonnie.

04:22.263 --> 04:23.963
[siren wailing]

04:23.965 --> 04:25.932
Damn it.

04:25.934 --> 04:27.300
I'm being pulled over.

04:27.302 --> 04:28.935
Stefan...

04:33.408 --> 04:34.574
[siren stops]

04:44.686 --> 04:46.919
Hands where I can see 'em!

04:46.921 --> 04:48.955
Step out of the car, now!

04:56.364 --> 04:57.964
[handcuffs clicking]

04:57.966 --> 05:00.166
CAROLINE: Stefan?

05:00.168 --> 05:01.801
Stefan!

05:01.803 --> 05:02.768
Stefan?

05:03.805 --> 05:05.771
I didn't even know you were in town.

05:05.773 --> 05:08.541
Yeah, well, Dorian needed
my help with something.

05:08.543 --> 05:11.310
Looks like he wasn't the only one.

05:11.312 --> 05:13.312
So what the hell happened?

05:13.314 --> 05:15.481
I don't know, but I'm telling you,

05:15.483 --> 05:18.284
I could feel the heat from the flames...

05:18.286 --> 05:21.120
hear the screams of all
those people burning.

05:21.122 --> 05:22.753
Are you sure it wasn't just a nightmare?

05:22.756 --> 05:24.654
You know, your mind
trying to work out that

05:24.657 --> 05:27.593
you almost rang the bell
and burned down Mystic Falls?

05:27.595 --> 05:29.562
No, Ric, this was different.

05:29.564 --> 05:31.898
It was like I was actually there.

05:31.900 --> 05:33.566
DORIAN: Maybe you were.

05:33.568 --> 05:36.536
And I don't think this
is just colonial bling.

05:36.538 --> 05:39.305
Based on the time period
and the local coven activity,

05:39.307 --> 05:41.207
I think this could be a witch talisman

05:41.209 --> 05:44.477
that's somehow tied to
the Maxwell bloodline.

05:44.479 --> 05:46.913
Maybe those weren't nightmares.

05:46.915 --> 05:48.981
Maybe they were memories.

05:48.983 --> 05:50.183
How is that even possible?

05:50.185 --> 05:51.317
ALARIC: Well, I've heard of

05:51.319 --> 05:52.418
Latvian witches using
something like that

05:52.420 --> 05:53.795
to contact the dead.

05:53.798 --> 05:55.398
You know, a way to create a psychic link

05:55.400 --> 05:57.156
between the living and their ancestors.

05:57.158 --> 05:58.691
Yeah, and that might
explain how you slept-walked

05:58.693 --> 05:59.725
your way into those tunnels.

05:59.727 --> 06:01.727
Okay, then who am I linked to?

06:01.729 --> 06:03.496
[cell phone rings]

06:03.498 --> 06:06.532
- If I had to guess...
- Hey.

06:06.534 --> 06:09.035
...I'd say the skeleton we
found in the artifact room.

06:09.037 --> 06:11.502
Some of the things you saw, he saw, too.

06:11.505 --> 06:13.339
He wrote about them in his journal.

06:13.341 --> 06:16.049
There are references to working
with a coven of Bennett witches.

06:16.052 --> 06:17.810
- Bennett?
- Yeah.

06:17.812 --> 06:20.713
I wonder if Bonnie would
know something about this.

06:20.715 --> 06:22.548
[phone beeps]

06:23.751 --> 06:25.785
Everything okay?

06:27.055 --> 06:28.754
No.

06:31.226 --> 06:33.759
No, it's...

06:33.761 --> 06:35.895
it's bad.

06:45.873 --> 06:47.773
[cell phone ringing]

06:48.643 --> 06:50.776
[phone beeps]

06:50.778 --> 06:52.411
He hasn't come back.

06:52.413 --> 06:53.579
That's because he's on his way

06:53.581 --> 06:55.932
to Rockland County Police Department.

06:55.935 --> 06:57.450
He's been arrested.

06:57.452 --> 06:58.918
Okay. That's good.

06:58.920 --> 07:01.087
In what world is that good?

07:01.089 --> 07:02.588
One where Stefan's human.

07:02.590 --> 07:04.290
His emotions are back.

07:04.292 --> 07:06.559
The memories of every drop
of blood he's ever spilled

07:06.561 --> 07:09.061
are gonna be doing a
square dance in his head.

07:09.063 --> 07:11.330
It's best he's not alone
with all this right now.

07:11.332 --> 07:13.766
I'll meet you there.

07:13.768 --> 07:15.501
You talk to Bonnie?

07:18.091 --> 07:20.339
I've left so many messages.

07:20.341 --> 07:22.608
She just won't answer her
phone... I don't get it.

07:22.610 --> 07:24.543
Sure you do.

07:24.545 --> 07:25.845
Think about it.

07:25.847 --> 07:29.482
Can you blame her?

07:29.484 --> 07:31.917
I'll call you when I'm close.

07:31.919 --> 07:33.119
[phone beeps]

07:35.690 --> 07:37.690
Forgive me.

07:37.692 --> 07:40.140
I let myself in.

07:40.143 --> 07:43.195
I came to offer my condolences.

07:43.197 --> 07:45.765
I'm sorry for your loss.

07:45.767 --> 07:47.366
I doubt that,

07:47.368 --> 07:49.235
seeing you're the reason Enzo's dead.

07:49.237 --> 07:50.736
I was referring to your brother.

07:50.738 --> 07:53.306
Our deal was for two

07:53.308 --> 07:54.640
immortal souls.

07:54.642 --> 07:57.310
Your friends found a loophole
when they made Stefan human,

07:57.312 --> 07:59.478
rendering our agreement null and void.

07:59.480 --> 08:01.547
You and your brother are now free.

08:01.549 --> 08:04.216
Well, if you're making house calls,

08:04.218 --> 08:06.285
I'm guessing it's not that easy.

08:06.287 --> 08:09.722
While you remain immortal,

08:09.724 --> 08:11.557
Stefan does not.

08:11.559 --> 08:13.959
Which means I'm free to end his life

08:13.961 --> 08:17.363
and recall his soul to
the fiery pits of my world

08:17.365 --> 08:19.198
whenever I choose.

08:19.200 --> 08:21.352
I'm thinking he should die at midnight.

08:21.355 --> 08:23.135
And the fact that
you're waiting tells me

08:23.137 --> 08:24.870
you want something more than Stefan.

08:26.307 --> 08:28.808
In fact, there is.

08:28.811 --> 08:30.809
I've taken an interest

08:30.812 --> 08:32.745
in local history.

08:32.746 --> 08:35.847
There's an 18th-century journal
written by Ethan Maxwell.

08:35.850 --> 08:38.616
I believe your friend, the
occult studies professor,

08:38.619 --> 08:40.119
has come into possession of it.

08:40.121 --> 08:42.488
That what you want? Hmm?

08:42.490 --> 08:44.056
A dusty old book?

08:44.058 --> 08:46.158
It's a small price to
pay for allowing Stefan

08:46.160 --> 08:48.761
to live out the remainder
of his human life,

08:48.763 --> 08:51.664
before he returns to me.

08:51.666 --> 08:53.499
Do we have a deal?

09:05.561 --> 09:07.827
[door buzzes]

09:12.292 --> 09:14.926
So who's Olivia Hayden?

09:19.274 --> 09:21.641
Waitress,

09:21.643 --> 09:24.344
working her way through college.

09:25.457 --> 09:27.948
Till you nearly decapitated her.

09:27.950 --> 09:30.483
How about Javier Ruiz?

09:30.485 --> 09:34.220
Pharmacist. Wife. Kid on the way.

09:36.351 --> 09:38.425
Kelly Parks.

09:38.427 --> 09:40.627
Robert Lansu.

09:41.463 --> 09:42.963
Tanya Handelman.

09:42.965 --> 09:45.225
Jeffrey Li.

09:45.228 --> 09:46.999
The system connected your fingerprints

09:47.002 --> 09:50.003
to 32 murders in the last two months.

09:50.005 --> 09:53.173
You sure you don't have
anything to say about that?

09:55.877 --> 09:58.044
[tea kettle whistling]

10:00.482 --> 10:02.749
ENZO [whispering]: <i>Bonnie.</i>

10:04.446 --> 10:06.286
<i>Bonnie Bennett.</i>

10:06.288 --> 10:08.788
<i>Help me.</i>

10:08.790 --> 10:09.789
<i>Bonnie.</i>

10:09.791 --> 10:10.991
Enzo?

10:10.993 --> 10:12.158
[knock on door]

10:15.197 --> 10:16.663
[whistling stops]

10:22.938 --> 10:24.537
Mom?

10:24.539 --> 10:25.869
[whispers]: Bonnie.

10:30.751 --> 10:33.060
Caroline called me.

10:34.548 --> 10:36.883
She told me what happened.

10:36.885 --> 10:39.953
I'm sorry.

10:39.955 --> 10:42.222
She said you didn't want to talk to her,

10:42.224 --> 10:44.557
and... she's hoping

10:44.559 --> 10:47.494
maybe you'll... talk to me?

11:00.308 --> 11:01.708
[sniffles]

11:06.415 --> 11:07.681
[exhales]

11:07.683 --> 11:09.015
[door buzzes]

11:09.604 --> 11:12.047
My apologies, Mr. Salvatore.

11:17.626 --> 11:20.126
You're free to go.

11:21.197 --> 11:24.664
Thank you. Please notify all
the other agents and officers

11:24.666 --> 11:27.233
this was all a terrible mix-up.

11:44.553 --> 11:46.886
What is all this?

11:46.888 --> 11:48.488
This is me.

11:48.490 --> 11:51.925
No. This is Cade.

11:51.927 --> 11:54.594
He made you do all this.

11:54.596 --> 11:57.063
And he's gonna expect me to continue.

11:57.065 --> 11:59.165
I made a deal.

12:02.537 --> 12:03.837
The deal's off.

12:03.839 --> 12:05.939
What do you mean?

12:05.941 --> 12:10.643
You're human, and
you're of no use to him.

12:10.645 --> 12:13.913
He's giving you until midnight,
and then he wants you dead.

12:15.717 --> 12:17.951
But don't worry.

12:17.953 --> 12:19.686
Damon's on it.

12:24.260 --> 12:25.826
Bonnie's not picking up.

12:25.829 --> 12:27.929
I've tried her five times.

12:30.899 --> 12:32.799
What are you doing here?

12:32.801 --> 12:35.835
I need to borrow a book,
the Maxwell family tell-all.

12:35.837 --> 12:37.937
I'm guessing it's been
out of print for a while.

12:37.939 --> 12:39.205
You mean this?

12:39.207 --> 12:40.974
Convenient.

12:40.976 --> 12:42.208
And yes.

12:42.211 --> 12:45.283
Why are you so interested in
my family tree all of a sudden?

12:45.286 --> 12:46.460
Haven't been able to sleep lately,

12:46.462 --> 12:48.514
and I thought that would do the trick.

12:48.517 --> 12:49.716
What's it to you?

12:49.718 --> 12:51.317
Well, Matt here has been getting visions

12:51.319 --> 12:53.956
because of that journal; and
you show up looking for it.

12:53.959 --> 12:55.355
Coincidence?

12:55.357 --> 12:57.023
I think not.

12:57.025 --> 12:59.492
So why don't you tell us
the real reason you want it.

12:59.494 --> 13:01.828
All right.

13:01.830 --> 13:05.031
I got about six hours and change
until Cade takes Stefan's life,

13:05.033 --> 13:06.699
unless I give him that book.

13:06.701 --> 13:07.702
What's he want with it?

13:07.705 --> 13:09.038
I don't know.

13:09.041 --> 13:11.336
But if it saves my
brother's life, I don't care.

13:11.339 --> 13:12.405
Sorry.

13:12.408 --> 13:13.820
You don't give the devil what he wants

13:13.822 --> 13:15.555
if you don't know why he wants it.

13:15.558 --> 13:17.610
I'm sorry, too, old buddy.

13:17.612 --> 13:19.679
But Stefan's in this mess because of me.

13:19.681 --> 13:23.116
So you're gonna have to kill me, again,

13:23.118 --> 13:25.385
if you want to stop me.

13:26.755 --> 13:28.488
Hmm.

13:28.490 --> 13:30.056
Okay.

13:30.058 --> 13:32.091
Fine. Have it your way.

13:32.093 --> 13:33.159
Mm-hmm.

13:44.715 --> 13:48.492
♪ Come on, come on ♪

13:48.494 --> 13:52.230
♪ Put your hands into the fire ♪

13:52.232 --> 13:56.300
♪ Explain, explain ♪

13:56.302 --> 14:00.171
♪ As I turn, I meet the power ♪

14:00.173 --> 14:03.674
♪ This time, this time ♪

14:03.676 --> 14:06.911
♪ Turning white and senses dying ♪

14:06.913 --> 14:09.413
♪ Pull up, pull up... ♪

14:09.415 --> 14:10.615
It's time.

14:10.617 --> 14:12.783
We have to return Enzo to the earth.

14:12.785 --> 14:15.720
We have to say good-bye.

14:17.456 --> 14:19.990
I don't think he wants me to.

14:21.961 --> 14:23.928
I still feel him.

14:26.148 --> 14:27.948
Like he's calling out to me.

14:30.703 --> 14:32.236
Or I'm losing my mind.

14:32.238 --> 14:33.671
Oh.

14:33.673 --> 14:36.407
No, honey. You're grieving.

14:36.409 --> 14:39.377
Ugh, this isn't grief.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.746
I know grief.

14:41.748 --> 14:43.247
This is different.

14:44.244 --> 14:46.851
If he's trying to reach out to me,

14:46.853 --> 14:48.953
there has to be a way to reach him.

14:48.955 --> 14:50.855
The Other Side is gone.

14:50.857 --> 14:52.890
And neither of us
have our magic anymore.

14:52.892 --> 14:55.927
It's best not to mess with such things.

14:55.929 --> 14:58.863
There must be a way.

14:58.865 --> 15:02.400
You came back here for a reason.

15:02.402 --> 15:04.135
Let this be it.

15:04.137 --> 15:07.505
♪ Turning white and senses dying ♪

15:07.507 --> 15:11.742
♪ Pull up, pull up ♪

15:11.744 --> 15:13.210
♪ From one extreme to another... ♪

15:13.212 --> 15:14.812
CAROLINE: Thank you.

15:14.814 --> 15:17.181
And you're going to erase every mention

15:17.183 --> 15:19.083
of Stefan Salvatore's
name from your system.

15:20.019 --> 15:23.487
♪ From the mountain to the air... ♪

15:26.092 --> 15:28.626
OFFICER: And when did
you last see your mom?

15:28.628 --> 15:30.061
GIRL: Yesterday.

15:30.063 --> 15:33.558
After school, she called and
said she was running late.

15:34.722 --> 15:37.146
She was showing somebody a house.

15:38.569 --> 15:40.469
This is her.

15:44.887 --> 15:46.499
[screaming]

15:46.502 --> 15:49.213
♪ From the mountain ♪

15:49.215 --> 15:51.615
♪ To the air... ♪

15:51.617 --> 15:53.684
What is it?

15:53.686 --> 15:56.087
I forced that girl's mother

15:56.089 --> 15:58.155
to change the deed to Bonnie's house.

16:00.359 --> 16:04.313
But I left her for dead
in the trunk of a car.

16:04.316 --> 16:06.917
They won't find that body for weeks.

16:06.920 --> 16:09.333
Is there someone we can
call? A family member?

16:09.335 --> 16:12.703
No. It's just me and my mom.

16:12.705 --> 16:17.174
♪ Come on, come on ♪

16:17.176 --> 16:19.810
♪ Put your hands into the fire... ♪

16:19.812 --> 16:21.846
I know.

16:21.848 --> 16:23.581
Let's go find her.

16:23.583 --> 16:25.549
♪ Come on. ♪

16:28.788 --> 16:30.955
[groaning softly]

16:39.999 --> 16:42.066
[heart monitor beeping steadily]

16:43.436 --> 16:45.469
Yeah, the clock is
ticking on Stefan's life,

16:45.471 --> 16:49.473
but by all means, let's
give Donovan a physical.

16:49.475 --> 16:52.209
Well, if we can figure out
why the journal's so important

16:52.212 --> 16:54.167
to Cade, maybe we can
figure out how to stop him.

16:54.170 --> 16:55.879
After that, it's all yours.

16:55.882 --> 16:57.464
Oh, yeah?

16:57.467 --> 16:59.950
How's your little science
experiment gonna do that, huh?

16:59.952 --> 17:01.419
We're gonna trigger Matt's visions

17:01.421 --> 17:03.754
by inducing a hypnotic state.

17:03.756 --> 17:06.457
If we're lucky, the
answer's in his head.

17:06.459 --> 17:08.092
That'd be a first.

17:08.094 --> 17:10.428
The sedative should be
kicking in. How you feeling?

17:10.430 --> 17:13.230
Like I'm on the back half of a 12-pack.

17:13.232 --> 17:14.298
ALARIC: That's good.

17:15.435 --> 17:17.902
I want you to focus on the metronome.

17:17.904 --> 17:18.903
[metronome ticking]

17:18.905 --> 17:20.669
And listen to the sound of my voice.

17:20.672 --> 17:22.204
I want you to close your eyes

17:22.208 --> 17:24.075
and relax.

17:24.077 --> 17:26.676
Now I'm gonna lead you down

17:26.679 --> 17:28.244
a long path.

17:28.247 --> 17:29.980
This may take a while.

17:29.982 --> 17:31.849
[metronome continues ticking]

17:33.554 --> 17:35.520
Or we'll just dive right in.

17:35.523 --> 17:37.694
ALARIC: Okay, Matt,
picture yourself there.

17:37.697 --> 17:39.023
Now tell me what you're seeing.

17:39.025 --> 17:40.825
[bell tolls]

17:40.827 --> 17:41.926
The bell.

17:41.928 --> 17:43.828
Maxwell's journal.

17:43.830 --> 17:46.462
<i>It's the old house where
the witches were burned.</i>

17:46.465 --> 17:49.166
But it's not old, it
looks like it's brand-new.

17:49.168 --> 17:50.968
[bell tolls]

17:50.970 --> 17:55.272
Mr. Maxwell, you are a true artist.

17:55.274 --> 17:57.908
You are too kind, Ms. Bennett.

17:57.910 --> 18:00.044
[bell tolls]

18:00.046 --> 18:02.413
My skills pale in
comparison to the magic

18:02.415 --> 18:04.115
your coven infused in its metal.

18:04.117 --> 18:06.784
Hmm. My mother was glad

18:06.786 --> 18:08.886
to receive your letter

18:08.888 --> 18:11.255
announcing the bell's completion.

18:11.257 --> 18:14.525
But not as glad as I was

18:14.527 --> 18:16.360
to decipher the information

18:16.362 --> 18:18.777
you had so cleverly hidden within.

18:20.266 --> 18:24.001
"Your courage will save us all."

18:24.003 --> 18:26.637
And soon we will be rid of
the vile, inhuman creatures

18:26.639 --> 18:28.405
stalking our woods.

18:28.407 --> 18:30.007
Have there been more attacks?

18:30.009 --> 18:31.442
Just last night.

18:31.444 --> 18:33.944
That makes nine of our community

18:33.946 --> 18:36.547
that's been slaughtered by these
nameless, faceless monsters.

18:36.549 --> 18:40.284
By this time tomorrow,
the ringing of your bell

18:40.286 --> 18:44.321
will drive those depraved
beasts from our lands.

18:44.323 --> 18:46.824
[siren singing in distance]

18:46.826 --> 18:49.393
[Sybil humming]

18:51.230 --> 18:53.297
Forgive my intrusion.

18:53.299 --> 18:55.065
But I'm in need of a metalsmith,

18:55.067 --> 18:57.902
and from what I've
been told, Mr. Maxwell,

18:57.904 --> 19:00.304
you are the finest in Virginia.

19:01.874 --> 19:04.808
It's Sybil. She's here.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.443
She wants Ethan to come with her.

19:06.445 --> 19:07.912
He can't resist her.

19:13.241 --> 19:14.908
Does any of this look familiar?

19:14.911 --> 19:16.554
Don't know. Maybe.

19:16.556 --> 19:18.455
It'll be dark soon.

19:18.457 --> 19:20.575
Damon's gonna come
through, okay? He will.

19:20.578 --> 19:21.926
Yeah? And then what?

19:21.928 --> 19:23.561
You can compel away all the evidence

19:23.563 --> 19:24.828
of what I've done.

19:24.830 --> 19:26.463
Doesn't change the fact that I did it.

19:26.465 --> 19:29.366
I can't just forget about
that and go cake-tasting.

19:30.269 --> 19:32.303
Is that what you think of me?

19:32.305 --> 19:33.737
[chuckles]

19:33.739 --> 19:35.906
That all I care about is our wedding?

19:35.908 --> 19:38.197
Look, I don't know what to think.

19:38.200 --> 19:40.076
I don't know how to
deal with what I want

19:40.079 --> 19:42.012
or what I thought I was gonna have.

19:43.349 --> 19:45.149
I don't know what to do.

19:48.780 --> 19:50.847
There.

19:57.396 --> 19:59.496
She survived.

20:01.867 --> 20:03.067
There's still a chance.

20:05.538 --> 20:07.238
But for how much longer?

20:07.240 --> 20:09.373
Let's go.

20:20.278 --> 20:21.911
[heart monitor beeping steadily]

20:21.913 --> 20:23.379
MATT: <i>We're in the caves.</i>

20:23.381 --> 20:24.914
<i>There's a door.</i>

20:26.418 --> 20:28.985
It's the room where
you found the journal.

20:34.544 --> 20:36.159
<i>It's full of the sirens' treasures.</i>

20:36.161 --> 20:38.594
<i>There's tools and weapons.</i>

20:41.483 --> 20:43.176
What is this?

20:44.309 --> 20:45.854
And what is it made from?

20:45.856 --> 20:47.889
Death.

20:47.891 --> 20:53.261
From when the ash and burn
of Cade was forged into glass

20:53.263 --> 20:55.931
by the fire of hell's creation.

20:57.301 --> 21:00.035
Surely you've heard of
the legend of Arcadius.

21:00.037 --> 21:01.273
No.

21:01.276 --> 21:04.796
You know him by another name: the devil.

21:08.303 --> 21:10.536
MATT: <i>Seline's there, too.</i>

21:14.201 --> 21:16.518
<i>She has the tuning fork.</i>

21:16.520 --> 21:18.853
They're forcing Ethan
to add it to the bell.

21:18.855 --> 21:21.189
When my master, Cade,

21:21.191 --> 21:24.960
learned of your bell's ability
to drive us from your lands,

21:24.962 --> 21:28.697
he devised an altogether
different purpose for it.

21:28.699 --> 21:29.998
What will it do?

21:30.000 --> 21:33.668
The twelfth ring will unleash hellfire,

21:33.670 --> 21:36.972
incinerating your entire village.

21:36.974 --> 21:39.541
You will not breathe a word of it.

21:42.967 --> 21:45.013
Come on!

21:45.015 --> 21:46.441
Cut to the chase!

21:46.444 --> 21:48.416
Where's the smoking
gun in this story, huh?

21:48.418 --> 21:50.385
Why is the journal so important?

21:50.387 --> 21:53.121
Hey, listen, he can't control
what he's seeing, Damon. Relax.

21:53.123 --> 21:55.257
[heart monitor beeping steadily]

21:59.909 --> 22:02.931
Enzo, we call on you.

22:02.933 --> 22:06.001
One who loves you is
reaching out to you.

22:06.003 --> 22:09.698
If you are among us,
please give us a sign.

22:10.994 --> 22:13.508
Enzo, if you are there,

22:13.510 --> 22:15.510
we are here to listen.

22:20.017 --> 22:22.050
[screaming]

22:22.052 --> 22:23.385
[screams]

22:26.523 --> 22:28.423
What are you doing?

22:28.425 --> 22:30.242
Oh, you were right.

22:30.245 --> 22:32.545
This is not grief.

22:32.548 --> 22:34.329
This is something different.

22:34.331 --> 22:36.798
I saw the moment of Enzo's death.

22:36.800 --> 22:38.533
I felt his pain.

22:38.535 --> 22:41.636
I don't know how that's
possible without magic.

22:41.638 --> 22:43.638
You must have opened a door.

22:43.640 --> 22:45.206
To where?

22:45.208 --> 22:47.442
To wherever Enzo is.

22:47.444 --> 22:49.377
Somewhere dark.

22:49.379 --> 22:53.114
Filled with suffering and emptiness.

22:54.651 --> 22:56.251
You mean hell?

22:56.253 --> 22:59.754
I don't know, but we
need to close that door.

22:59.756 --> 23:02.123
We need to bury him.

23:02.125 --> 23:04.993
If Enzo's in there and we
bury him, he'll be trapped.

23:04.995 --> 23:06.728
There must be a way to free him.

23:06.730 --> 23:07.962
No.

23:07.964 --> 23:09.764
Whatever darkness you reached into

23:09.766 --> 23:11.433
is reaching back for you.

23:13.594 --> 23:15.928
ENZO: <i>Bonnie.</i>

23:15.930 --> 23:17.963
I'm not gonna leave you in there.

23:17.965 --> 23:20.065
I'll find a way.

23:20.067 --> 23:22.401
[ears ringing]

23:23.295 --> 23:24.770
Bonnie!

23:24.772 --> 23:26.939
Karen?

23:31.312 --> 23:33.040
Hey, you're gonna be okay.

23:33.043 --> 23:34.613
[gasps] Oh, God, no!

23:34.615 --> 23:37.182
No, no, no, no. No, no.
It's okay. I'm here to help.

23:37.184 --> 23:39.051
Get away from me! It's
okay, I'm here to help you.

23:39.053 --> 23:40.152
Caroline, she's here!

23:40.154 --> 23:41.120
[grunts]

23:42.423 --> 23:43.522
Stefan?

23:43.524 --> 23:45.257
STEFAN: No, no, no, no. Save her.

23:45.259 --> 23:46.258
Save her.

23:46.260 --> 23:47.626
Now.

23:48.562 --> 23:50.062
[grunts]

23:50.064 --> 23:51.730
Come on, you have to drink.

23:51.732 --> 23:52.865
Drink!

23:52.867 --> 23:54.032
[sucking]

23:54.034 --> 23:55.167
There we go. Good.

23:55.169 --> 23:57.569
[groans]

23:57.571 --> 23:58.804
You're gonna be fine.

23:58.806 --> 23:59.972
Just stay here.

24:01.327 --> 24:02.593
[flesh rips]

24:04.745 --> 24:06.612
[gags, coughs]

24:06.614 --> 24:08.447
Oh, God.

24:08.449 --> 24:09.915
The cure is in you.

24:09.917 --> 24:11.183
[coughs]

24:11.185 --> 24:13.552
My blood won't work. I can't save you.

24:13.554 --> 24:15.754
- [Stefan gagging]
- I can't save you.

24:18.859 --> 24:21.593
The witches are gathering
for the ringing of the bell.

24:24.698 --> 24:28.100
<i>Ethan can't warn Bea,
because he's been sirened</i>

24:28.102 --> 24:29.501
<i>not to tell her.</i>

24:30.771 --> 24:32.638
What did that woman want?

24:32.640 --> 24:34.606
I cannot say.

24:34.608 --> 24:37.276
But we tell each other everything.

24:37.278 --> 24:40.579
I know. But I cannot say.

24:40.581 --> 24:43.582
I see.

24:51.283 --> 24:53.817
I cannot say.

24:57.598 --> 25:01.233
MATT: <i>He's encoded a message for her.</i>

25:01.235 --> 25:03.468
<i>He can't stop himself.</i>

25:03.470 --> 25:06.605
<i>He's been sirened to ring the
bell and destroy the town.</i>

25:08.450 --> 25:10.917
"The bell has been corrupted."

25:11.745 --> 25:15.013
"The twelfth ring will bring hellfire."

25:15.849 --> 25:16.782
No!

25:16.784 --> 25:18.984
- [bell tolls]
- MATT: <i> One.</i>

25:18.986 --> 25:20.385
Oh! [groaning]

25:20.387 --> 25:22.821
- [bell tolls]
- MATT: <i> Two.</i>

25:23.624 --> 25:25.991
- [bell tolls]
- <i>Three.</i>

25:25.993 --> 25:27.593
The bell has been corrupted!

25:27.595 --> 25:29.161
It will destroy us all!

25:29.163 --> 25:30.529
[groans]

25:30.531 --> 25:32.231
[bell tolls]

25:32.233 --> 25:33.865
We must stop it!

25:33.867 --> 25:35.667
Stand as one!

25:35.669 --> 25:37.243
Chant with me!

25:39.206 --> 25:42.908
<i>Phesmotos, motus, incendarios.</i>

25:42.910 --> 25:47.079
<i>Phesmotos, motus, incendarios.</i>

25:47.081 --> 25:48.614
[gasps]

25:48.616 --> 25:50.148
They're trying to stop it.

25:50.751 --> 25:52.084
<i>Twelve!</i>

25:55.022 --> 25:56.855
[Matt groaning]

25:58.659 --> 26:01.093
We got to bring him out!
He can't take much more.

26:01.095 --> 26:02.160
Matt? Matt!

26:02.162 --> 26:03.695
- [groaning]
- Matt!

26:03.697 --> 26:05.430
Matt, come on. Matt!

26:05.432 --> 26:07.099
Matt! Matt!

26:07.101 --> 26:09.473
MATT: <i>The witches are trying
to hold back the flames</i>

26:09.476 --> 26:10.535
<i>and save the town.</i>

26:10.537 --> 26:12.404
[people yelling]

26:15.442 --> 26:16.775
They're dying.

26:16.777 --> 26:18.076
Sacrificing themselves

26:18.078 --> 26:19.444
<i>to stop the fire.</i>

26:19.446 --> 26:20.579
[yelling continues]

26:20.581 --> 26:22.748
No!

26:22.750 --> 26:24.516
I think he's having a heart attack.

26:24.518 --> 26:25.517
Come on, Matt.

26:25.519 --> 26:26.585
DAMON: Hey!

26:26.587 --> 26:27.786
Give him my blood.

26:28.789 --> 26:30.589
[monitor flatlines]

26:30.591 --> 26:32.624
Do it!

26:33.460 --> 26:35.761
[door beeps]

26:35.763 --> 26:36.795
Will that work?

26:36.797 --> 26:39.231
If it repairs the heart in time.

26:39.233 --> 26:41.099
[sucking]

26:42.770 --> 26:44.803
[heart monitor beeping steadily]

26:47.741 --> 26:50.942
<i>[people screaming]</i>

26:55.949 --> 26:58.917
[bell clanging]

27:02.523 --> 27:05.724
MATT: <i>Bea... Bea.</i>

27:14.868 --> 27:16.368
[heart monitor beeping steadily]

27:16.370 --> 27:17.803
[whispers]: Beatrice.

27:17.805 --> 27:21.540
Beatrice, she has a
plan to stop the sirens.

27:31.418 --> 27:33.251
<i>Averte oculos</i>

27:33.253 --> 27:36.521
<i>tuos a quo exitus.</i>

27:36.523 --> 27:39.458
<i>Hunc exitus ab auribos.</i>

27:43.997 --> 27:46.264
You did it. They're trapped.

27:46.266 --> 27:48.700
As are you, Mr. Maxwell.

27:48.702 --> 27:50.435
You made the bell.

27:50.437 --> 27:53.205
And the witches cursed it, so
the blood of a hundred souls

27:53.207 --> 27:54.887
are on your hands.

27:54.890 --> 27:57.333
You and Beatrice are doomed to hell.

27:58.731 --> 28:01.654
There is one way you can
escape the eternal fire.

28:03.208 --> 28:05.851
Release our master Cade from hell

28:05.853 --> 28:08.387
and allow him to walk the Earth.

28:08.389 --> 28:09.988
Then kill him.

28:10.724 --> 28:12.224
No.

28:12.226 --> 28:15.160
We cannot allow the
devil to walk the Earth.

28:15.162 --> 28:17.362
SELINE: Ethan,

28:17.364 --> 28:21.400
if your friend will not free
us, then you must kill her.

28:21.402 --> 28:22.701
No.

28:24.638 --> 28:27.706
[singing siren song]

28:34.181 --> 28:36.314
[siren song continues]

28:38.318 --> 28:40.018
<i>Motus!</i>

28:43.848 --> 28:46.591
She's trapped him in the room
where you found his bones.

28:47.995 --> 28:49.060
Bea!

28:49.062 --> 28:50.695
Bea, open the door!

28:50.697 --> 28:52.564
[knocking] No, Bea!

28:52.566 --> 28:54.666
Don't leave me! Bea!

28:54.668 --> 28:56.835
I know their secret, Bea! It's in here!

28:56.837 --> 28:58.470
I know how to kill the devil.

28:58.472 --> 29:00.472
They will not allow me

29:00.474 --> 29:02.407
to tell you what I've discovered!

29:02.409 --> 29:04.576
I cannot say!

29:04.578 --> 29:07.145
Bea!

29:07.147 --> 29:10.115
I know how we can kill the devil.

29:10.117 --> 29:12.617
But I cannot say.

29:12.619 --> 29:14.853
Do you understand?!

29:22.177 --> 29:25.211
MATT: <i>He's trying to tell
her the only way he can.</i>

29:32.978 --> 29:34.277
It's in the journal.

29:36.243 --> 29:37.442
Where is it?

29:37.444 --> 29:39.277
Where's Damon?

29:47.784 --> 29:51.994
Bonnie, stay with me.
Please, Bonnie. No!

30:07.395 --> 30:09.162
[whispers]: Bonnie.

30:10.598 --> 30:13.332
No! Enzo!

30:13.334 --> 30:15.735
No! Enzo! Bonnie!

30:15.737 --> 30:17.436
[Bonnie yelling]

30:17.438 --> 30:18.971
Bonnie!

30:18.973 --> 30:20.506
I had to!

30:20.508 --> 30:22.675
I had to, baby.

30:22.677 --> 30:24.477
I had to destroy every part of him.

30:24.479 --> 30:26.646
It was the only way to
break the connection...

30:26.648 --> 30:28.414
He was trying to reach me!

30:28.416 --> 30:29.882
No, Bonnie.

30:29.884 --> 30:31.984
He didn't open that door, you did.

30:34.072 --> 30:37.623
I have failed you in so
many ways as a mother.

30:37.625 --> 30:39.392
But I will not

30:39.394 --> 30:41.794
let you destroy yourself.

30:41.796 --> 30:45.331
He's alone in darkness.

30:45.333 --> 30:47.934
And he wouldn't want
to drag you in with him.

30:47.936 --> 30:49.168
You know that.

30:49.170 --> 30:51.637
He loved you.

30:53.648 --> 30:55.648
He wouldn't want you to suffer.

30:57.312 --> 30:58.844
You got to let him go.

30:58.846 --> 31:02.148
Okay, baby? You got to let him go.

31:03.551 --> 31:05.669
You got to say good-bye.

31:05.672 --> 31:07.805
[crying]

31:13.595 --> 31:15.528
[Stefan gasps]

31:18.299 --> 31:19.765
Where's Karen?

31:19.767 --> 31:21.033
- Where is she?
- She's okay.

31:21.035 --> 31:23.569
I compelled her to wait by
the road for the ambulance.

31:23.571 --> 31:26.105
They're on their way. Just hang with me.

31:26.107 --> 31:28.040
[groaning]: Caroline, it doesn't matter.

31:28.042 --> 31:30.743
Today, tomorrow... I know where
I'm going and I deserve it.

31:30.745 --> 31:32.845
- No, you don't, okay?
- Yes, I do.

31:32.847 --> 31:34.180
You saved that woman's life.

31:34.182 --> 31:35.834
Doesn't matter. It's just one person.

31:35.837 --> 31:37.316
You are not going to give up.

31:37.318 --> 31:39.685
You are going to keep
fighting. You are going to live.

31:39.687 --> 31:41.254
You are going to stay alive

31:41.256 --> 31:43.155
so you can make all of this right.

31:43.157 --> 31:44.790
- [gasps]
- Stefan.

31:44.792 --> 31:46.092
[siren approaching]

31:46.094 --> 31:48.561
Stefan.

31:49.756 --> 31:51.923
God.

31:57.479 --> 31:58.904
Cutting it pretty close.

31:58.906 --> 32:00.673
Story of my life.

32:06.724 --> 32:08.924
How do I know you're
gonna keep up your end?

32:08.926 --> 32:11.226
You don't.

32:15.866 --> 32:17.266
[sighs]

32:17.268 --> 32:19.434
Thank you.

32:22.606 --> 32:24.640
Your brother's free to live out the term

32:24.642 --> 32:26.208
of his human life.

32:26.210 --> 32:29.011
I hope he makes the most
of his borrowed time.

32:29.013 --> 32:32.180
Just between us bad guys...

32:32.182 --> 32:34.750
has anyone ever...

32:34.752 --> 32:36.318
earned their way out?

32:36.320 --> 32:38.987
Hmm.

32:38.989 --> 32:41.356
I wouldn't want to give you false hope.

33:06.377 --> 33:09.741
- Mom! I'm so glad you're okay.
- Hey, baby.

33:09.744 --> 33:14.951
♪ This house has many rooms ♪

33:14.953 --> 33:17.053
♪ Filled with dust ♪

33:17.055 --> 33:19.055
♪ And pieces of you... ♪

33:19.057 --> 33:22.792
Okay, I got antibiotics,
anti-inflammatory

33:22.794 --> 33:23.861
and pain meds.

33:23.864 --> 33:26.796
I guess you wouldn't know if
you're allergic to anything.

33:26.798 --> 33:31.667
Look, um... I know it
wasn't about the wedding.

33:31.669 --> 33:33.102
I didn't mean that.

33:33.104 --> 33:34.804
I know.

33:34.806 --> 33:36.906
It's just when I think
about what our lives

33:36.908 --> 33:38.908
are supposed to look like now,

33:38.910 --> 33:41.310
I just can't see it.

33:41.312 --> 33:44.947
Ten years from now... 20, 50...

33:44.949 --> 33:47.250
we're gonna be living
entirely different lives,

33:47.252 --> 33:51.888
and we can't just... ignore that.

33:51.890 --> 33:57.693
But... it doesn't
mean we have to just...

33:57.695 --> 34:02.031
throw all this away because it's
not what we wanted or expected.

34:02.033 --> 34:05.201
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh... ♪

34:05.203 --> 34:09.092
I just have no idea
how to make this right.

34:13.311 --> 34:15.812
I don't either.

34:15.813 --> 34:19.958
♪ Ooh, ooh... ♪

34:19.960 --> 34:23.418
But I know where you can start.

34:23.420 --> 34:29.192
♪ Ah, ooh, ah, ooh ♪

34:29.194 --> 34:34.263
♪ What have we become... ♪

34:34.264 --> 34:37.266
How long have you been waiting there?

34:37.268 --> 34:39.034
Not long.

34:39.036 --> 34:41.337
- Liar.
- Seriously.

34:41.339 --> 34:43.505
I've been hypnotized, almost
died of a heart attack,

34:43.507 --> 34:45.641
and lost the only means
of killing the devil,

34:45.643 --> 34:48.385
and then I came here

34:48.388 --> 34:51.746
to tell you how sorry I am about Enzo.

34:51.748 --> 34:54.283
The last part being the most important.

34:56.120 --> 34:59.920
I know sorry doesn't change
anything or bring him back.

34:59.923 --> 35:01.524
Believe me, I know what it's like

35:01.526 --> 35:02.967
to be on the other end of one of these.

35:02.969 --> 35:04.560
There's nothing I can say or do.

35:04.562 --> 35:06.229
I don't think I can do this.

35:06.231 --> 35:07.763
I do.

35:07.765 --> 35:11.968
You're one of the
strongest people I know.

35:11.970 --> 35:13.870
I think I know where you get

35:13.872 --> 35:15.238
some of that strength from.

35:15.240 --> 35:16.672
It's a long story.

35:16.674 --> 35:18.774
I'll tell you when you're up for it.

35:18.776 --> 35:22.478
Turns out, our families go way back.

35:22.480 --> 35:24.814
I never truly appreciated what badasses

35:24.816 --> 35:26.349
you Bennett witches were.

35:26.351 --> 35:29.585
Too bad I don't have my magic anymore.

35:29.587 --> 35:32.722
If I did, none of this
would be happening.

35:32.724 --> 35:35.925
And I could've saved Enzo.

35:35.927 --> 35:37.693
[sighs]

35:39.530 --> 35:42.465
[sniffles]

35:42.467 --> 35:47.503
Try and find comfort in
the fact that Enzo loved you

35:47.505 --> 35:50.706
and he will always be with you.

35:57.645 --> 36:00.750
Call if you need me.

36:00.752 --> 36:02.451
Thanks.

36:26.945 --> 36:30.112
How's it feel to be a mere mortal?

36:30.114 --> 36:33.149
Uh, it... hurts.

36:34.385 --> 36:35.885
Definitely hurts.

36:35.888 --> 36:39.555
I heard they pumped you
full of three pints of blood.

36:39.557 --> 36:41.406
I hope you saved me some.

36:42.894 --> 36:45.528
It's a good thing that wasn't
funny, otherwise I'd be, uh...

36:45.530 --> 36:48.064
[sniffles] ...ripping my stitches.

36:48.066 --> 36:49.398
Well, why don't you take a seat.

36:49.400 --> 36:51.155
I poured you a
painkiller-friendly drink,

36:51.158 --> 36:52.435
and I'll sit with you

36:52.437 --> 36:55.338
and remind you how badly you
always wanted to be human.

36:55.340 --> 36:57.506
I'm gonna have to pass. I...

36:57.508 --> 37:00.609
I just came home to change
before I go to Bonnie's.

37:00.611 --> 37:03.346
I spent the last hour trying to...

37:03.348 --> 37:05.514
figure out what I was gonna say to her.

37:05.516 --> 37:07.283
What'd you come up with?

37:09.053 --> 37:10.853
Nothing.

37:10.855 --> 37:13.721
Mm, nothing to say.

37:13.724 --> 37:15.724
If I can't figure out
a way to forgive myself,

37:15.727 --> 37:17.495
I can't expect her to.

37:17.498 --> 37:20.432
Well, you'd be surprised.

37:20.434 --> 37:22.601
Bonnie's a much better
person than you or me.

37:22.603 --> 37:25.904
I'm not saying it won't take time.

37:25.906 --> 37:28.373
Clock doesn't start ticking
until you say the words.

37:31.178 --> 37:34.412
Well, regardless of how that goes,

37:34.414 --> 37:37.249
I just wanted to say thank you...

37:37.251 --> 37:39.184
for saving my life.

37:40.621 --> 37:42.354
No, that...

37:42.356 --> 37:45.490
that's no big deal.

37:45.492 --> 37:47.759
I do that 'cause it's Tuesday.

37:47.761 --> 37:50.962
Still, it gave me the chance to...

37:50.964 --> 37:52.798
undo all the damage that I've done.

37:52.800 --> 37:54.166
Yeah.

37:54.168 --> 37:57.302
I've got some undoing of my own to do.

38:00.805 --> 38:04.073
Do you think that
there's a chance for us?

38:06.367 --> 38:08.200
For redemption?

38:14.433 --> 38:16.500
Absolutely.

38:19.827 --> 38:21.359
Get to it.

38:35.275 --> 38:36.408
Hey, Dorian.

38:36.410 --> 38:38.155
So, I'm, uh, so sorry

38:38.158 --> 38:39.444
it got crazy around here today.

38:39.446 --> 38:41.530
What was it you needed my help with?

38:46.486 --> 38:48.954
You know what, it can
wait till tomorrow.

38:48.956 --> 38:52.157
Looks like you have
bigger things to deal with.

39:00.576 --> 39:04.378
Do you have any idea what you've done?

39:04.381 --> 39:06.771
Yeah.

39:06.773 --> 39:09.374
I saved my brother, Ric.

39:09.376 --> 39:10.742
No apologies.

39:10.744 --> 39:13.478
He's human,

39:13.480 --> 39:15.714
and if I'm lucky, I have
about 80 something years

39:15.716 --> 39:16.982
to make peace with the fact

39:16.984 --> 39:18.717
that he's gonna die one day.

39:18.719 --> 39:21.486
All I could do was make
sure that day wasn't today.

39:21.488 --> 39:24.256
Why do you only seem to care
about loss when it's your own?

39:24.258 --> 39:27.893
Because... say it with
me, Ric... I'm selfish.

39:27.895 --> 39:31.029
You have absolutely no idea...

39:31.031 --> 39:33.131
how important that journal was.

39:33.133 --> 39:34.666
I'm gonna take a shot and say

39:34.668 --> 39:37.170
that it was an instruction
manual to kill Cade.

39:37.173 --> 39:40.071
Oh, so you knew? And you
gave it to him anyway.

39:40.073 --> 39:42.908
Yup. Because I know how it ends.

39:44.611 --> 39:46.011
Come on.

39:46.013 --> 39:48.313
Grab your blindfold and your headphones.

40:00.794 --> 40:02.727
[exhales]

40:05.730 --> 40:07.930
[Taser crackles, Stefan grunts]

40:11.772 --> 40:13.405
DAMON: <i>Sybil sure loved</i>

40:13.407 --> 40:15.573
to hear herself talk.

40:15.575 --> 40:17.238
But...

40:17.241 --> 40:20.345
in all that blathering,
she did mention that she had

40:20.347 --> 40:22.447
an insurance policy against Cade.

40:23.949 --> 40:25.754
I'm betting this is it.

40:28.655 --> 40:31.556
Oh, yeah? How sure are you?

40:31.558 --> 40:33.458
60/40.

40:33.460 --> 40:35.126
But a relic of Cade's creation,

40:35.128 --> 40:38.229
that is the means to destroy him?

40:38.231 --> 40:40.665
Now, that has a certain poetry to it.

40:41.401 --> 40:43.435
Ah.

40:43.437 --> 40:45.270
Admit it.

40:45.272 --> 40:47.105
I did pretty good.

40:50.510 --> 40:53.411
Now... [sighs] you got to
have a bottle of bourbon

40:53.413 --> 40:55.080
stashed in here somewhere.

40:55.082 --> 40:57.006
I say we grab that,

40:57.009 --> 40:58.912
exchange a few half-assed apologies

40:58.915 --> 41:02.153
for all the crappy things
we've done to each other...

41:02.155 --> 41:04.789
and make a plan to kill the devil.

41:06.126 --> 41:08.393
Yeah, sorry to interrupt.

41:09.914 --> 41:13.649
But what if I told you
I had a better idea?

